   "source": [
    "# Assuming df is your DataFrame\n",
    "value_counts = df['Room_type'].value_counts()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a mask for categories with count less than 30\n",
    "mask = value_counts < 30\n",
    "\n",
    "# Replace categories with 'Other' based on the mask\n",
    "df['Room_type'] = df['Room_type'].apply(lambda x: 'other' if mask[x] else x)\n"
   ]

    "for col in dfi:\n",
    "    if plotnumber<=5:\n",
    "        ax=plt.subplot(3,2,plotnumber)\n",
    "        sns.distplot(dfi[col])\n",
    "        plt.xlabel(col,fontsize=12)\n",
    "    plotnumber+=1\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7904df38",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "From the above graph we can see that\n",
    "- Price is highly right skewed\n",
    "- number of review is highly right skewed\n",
    "- user ratings is highly left skewed\n",
    "- star sating is categorical and highest frequency is for 4.\n",
    "- review score is highly left skewed."
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 386,
   "id": "9320f455",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x720 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Calculate the value counts for the Room_type column\n",
    "x_counts = dfo['Room_type'].value_counts()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Select the top 5 categories\n",
    "top_5_categories = x_counts.head(5)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a new DataFrame with the top 5 categories and a \"Rest\" category\n",
    "df_modified = pd.DataFrame({'Room_type': top_5_categories.index, 'Count': top_5_categories.values})\n",
    "rest_count = x_counts.sum() - top_5_categories.sum()\n",
    "df_modified = df_modified.append({'Room_type': 'Rest', 'Count': rest_count}, ignore_index=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a pie chart\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))\n",
    "plt.pie(df_modified['Count'], labels=df_modified['Room_type'], autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=45)\n",
    "plt.title('Distribution of Room type (Top 5)')\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
   ]
  },

    "df['average_rating_per_city_star'] = df.groupby(['cities', 'star rating'])['user ratings'].transform('mean')\n",
    "df['average_price_per_room_hotel'] = df.groupby(['Room_type', 'Hotel'])['price'].transform('mean')\n",
    "df['average_price_per_hotel'] = df.groupby('Hotel name')['price'].transform('mean')\n",
    "df['average_price_per_city_star'] = df.groupby(['cities', 'star rating'])['price'].transform('mean')"
   ]
  },

   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Removing skewness"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9d7a5a0b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### For df"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 536,
   "id": "dee9505e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Step 1: Calculate skewness for each feature\n",
    "skewness = x1.apply(lambda x1: x1.skew())\n",
    "\n",
    "skew_threshold = 0.5\n",
    "\n",
    "# Step 3: Identify highly skewed features and apply a transformation (e.g., log)\n",
    "highly_skewed_features = skewness[skewness > skew_threshold].index\n",
    "\n",
    "for feature in highly_skewed_features:\n",
    "    x1[feature] = np.log1p(x1[feature])\n",
    "    \n",
    "    \n",
    "for feature in highly_skewed_features:\n",
    "    x1[feature] = x1[feature] ** (1/3)# Cubic root transformation\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 537,
   "id": "4ba66cda",
   "metadata": {},

    "# Step 1: Calculate skewness for each feature\n",
    "skewness = x2.apply(lambda x2: x2.skew())\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "skew_threshold = 0.5\n",
    "\n",
    "# Step 3: Identify highly skewed features and apply a transformation(e.g., log)\n",
    "highly_skewed_features = skewness[skewness > skew_threshold].index\n",
    "\n",
    "for feature in highly_skewed_features:\n",
    "    x2[feature] = np.log1p(x2[feature]) \n",
    "    \n",
    "for feature in highly_skewed_features:\n",
    "    x2[feature] = x2[feature] ** (1/3) # Cubic root transformation\n"
   ]

   ],
   "source": [
    "# Finding VIF in each scaled column i.e x.shape[1]/(1/(1-r2))\n",
    "from statsmodels.stats.outliers_influence import variance_inflation_factor\n",
    "vif1=pd.DataFrame()\n",
    "vif1['VIF values']=[variance_inflation_factor(x1.values,i)for i in range(len(x1.columns))]\n",
    "vif1['Features']=x1.columns\n",
    "vif1\n"
   ]
  },

    "# Model building Regression(Price)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 548,
   "id": "037431d0",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# importing necessary libraries\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import mean_absolute_error,mean_squared_error,r2_score\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f7ac6f65",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Best random state"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 549,
   "id": "f0d75eff",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Best accuracy is 0.428088478017418 at random_state 26\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "random_states = range(1, 200)\n",
    "r2_scores = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for rs in random_states:\n",
    "    x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(x1, y1, test_size=0.35, random_state=rs)\n",
    "    LR = LinearRegression()\n",
    "    LR.fit(x_train, y_train)\n",
    "    pred = LR.predict(x_test)\n",
    "    r2 = r2_score(y_test, pred)\n",
    "    r2_scores.append(r2)\n",
    "\n",
    "max_r2 = max(r2_scores)\n",
    "max_rs = random_states[r2_scores.index(max_r2)]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Best accuracy is\", max_r2, \"at random_state\", max_rs)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7a3c1f30",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Train Test Split"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 550,
   "id": "b3280f96",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(x1, y1, test_size=0.35, random_state=max_rs)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 551,
   "id": "5ad3a215",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import Ridge,Lasso,RidgeCV,LassoCV\n",
    "from sklearn.svm import SVR\n",
    "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor\n",
    "from sklearn.ensemble import GradientBoostingRegressor\n",
    "from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeRegressor\n",
    "from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsRegressor\n",
    "from sklearn.ensemble import AdaBoostRegressor\n",
    "from xgboost import XGBRegressor "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 552,
   "id": "b1aed9a9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "training_r2_score = []\n",
    "testing_r2_score = []"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 553,
   "id": "e2af5584",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def model_prediction(model):\n",
    "    model.fit(x_train,y_train)\n",
    "    y_pred = model.predict(x_train)\n",
    "    pred = model.predict(x_test)\n",
    "    a = r2_score(y_train,y_pred)*100\n",
    "    b = r2_score(y_test,pred)*100\n",
    "    training_r2_score.append(a)\n",
    "    testing_r2_score.append(b)\n",
    "    print(f\"R2_Score of {model} model on Training Data is:\",a)\n",
    "    print(f\"R2_Score of {model} model on Testing Data is:\",b)\n",
    "    print(\"\\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Mean Absolute Error of {model} model is:\",mean_absolute_error(y_test,pred))\n",
    "    print(f\"Mean Square Error of {model} model is:\", mean_squared_error(y_test,pred))\n",
    "    print(f\"Squarroot Mean Square Error  {model} model is:\",np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test,pred)))\n",
    "    print(\"\\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 554,
   "id": "4cddda41",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

     "name": "stdout",

    "from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a570e040",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Finding best CV"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 568,
   "id": "73c0d17c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "           mean           std\n",
      "2 -7.615040e+08  3.833357e+08\n",
      "3 -7.363179e+08  3.627716e+08\n",
      "4 -7.281990e+08  4.004281e+08\n",
      "5 -8.238417e+08  5.115659e+08\n",
      "6 -7.488363e+08  5.178900e+08\n",
      "7 -7.354584e+08  5.621314e+08\n",
      "8 -7.190135e+08  4.552824e+08\n",
      "9 -7.275742e+08  5.354001e+08\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "num_folds_range = range(2,10)\n",
    "\n",
    "model = LinearRegression()\n",
    "\n",
    "fold_performance = {}\n",
    "\n",
    "for num_folds in num_folds_range:\n",
    "    scores = cross_val_score(model, x1, y1, cv=num_folds, scoring='neg_mean_squared_error')  # or 'r2' for coefficient of determination\n",
    "    fold_performance[num_folds] = {\n",
    "        'mean': np.mean(scores),\n",
    "        'std': np.std(scores)\n",
    "    }\n",
    "    \n",
    "df_fold_performance = pd.DataFrame(fold_performance).transpose()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(df_fold_performance)"
   ]
  },

    "## RandomForestRegressor"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 585,

   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "model1=RandomForestRegressor()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 586,
   "id": "c2895481",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "{'criterion': 'absolute_error',\n",
       " 'max_features': 'sqrt',\n",
       " 'min_samples_split': 6,\n",
       " 'n_estimators': 20}"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 586,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }

    "# Model building Regression(Review score)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 617,
   "id": "45e01284",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Best accuracy is 0.7088246512025784 at random_state 131\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "random_states = range(1, 200)\n",
    "r2_scores = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for rs in random_states:\n",
    "    x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(x2, y2, test_size=0.30, random_state=rs)\n",
    "    LR = LinearRegression()\n",
    "    LR.fit(x_train, y_train)\n",
    "    pred = LR.predict(x_test)\n",
    "    r2 = r2_score(y_test, pred)\n",
    "    r2_scores.append(r2)\n",
    "\n",
    "max_r2 = max(r2_scores)\n",
    "max_rs = random_states[r2_scores.index(max_r2)]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Best accuracy is\", max_r2, \"at random_state\", max_rs)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 618,
   "id": "b458611f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(x2, y2, test_size=0.30, random_state=max_rs)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 619,
   "id": "9deb8892",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "training_r2_score1 = []\n",
    "testing_r2_score1 = []"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 620,
   "id": "fe723cfa",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def model_prediction(model):\n",
    "    model.fit(x_train,y_train)\n",
    "    y_pred = model.predict(x_train)\n",
    "    pred = model.predict(x_test)\n",
    "    a = r2_score(y_train,y_pred)*100\n",
    "    b = r2_score(y_test,pred)*100\n",
    "    training_r2_score1.append(a)\n",
    "    testing_r2_score1.append(b)\n",
    "    print(f\"R2_Score of {model} model on Training Data is:\",a)\n",
    "    print(f\"R2_Score of {model} model on Testing Data is:\",b)\n",
    "    print(\"\\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Mean Absolute Error of {model} model is:\",mean_absolute_error(y_test,pred))\n",
    "    print(f\"Mean Square Error of {model} model is:\", mean_squared_error(y_test,pred))\n",
    "    print(f\"Squarroot Mean Square Error  {model} model is:\",np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test,pred)))\n",
    "    print(\"\\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 621,
   "id": "8608fec9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",

      "R2_Score of LinearRegression() model on Testing Data is: 70.88246512025785\n",
      "\n",
      "------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
      "Mean Absolute Error of LinearRegression() model is: 0.37368038880434856\n",

      "Squarroot Mean Square Error  LinearRegression() model is: 0.5069745077317548\n",
      "\n",
      "------------------------------------------------------------------------\n"
     ]
    }

    "from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 634,
   "id": "3c6d7ae2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "       mean       std\n",
      "2 -0.380850  0.015988\n",
      "3 -0.358463  0.068236\n",
      "4 -0.360939  0.086949\n",
      "5 -0.360721  0.103892\n",
      "6 -0.356133  0.094195\n",
      "7 -0.320649  0.079241\n",
      "8 -0.316401  0.102528\n",
      "9 -0.308322  0.089766\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "num_folds_range = range(2,10)\n",
    "\n",
    "model = LinearRegression()\n",
    "\n",
    "fold_performance = {}\n",
    "\n",
    "for num_folds in num_folds_range:\n",
    "    scores = cross_val_score(model, x2, y2, cv=num_folds, scoring='neg_mean_squared_error')  # or 'r2' for coefficient of determination\n",
    "    fold_performance[num_folds] = {\n",
    "        'mean': np.mean(scores),\n",
    "        'std': np.std(scores)\n",
    "    }\n",
    "    \n",
    "df_fold_performance = pd.DataFrame(fold_performance).transpose()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(df_fold_performance)"
   ]
  },

    "categories = ['Poor', 'Pleasant', 'Good', 'Very Good', 'Superb']\n",
    "bins = [0, 3, 5, 7, 9, 10] \n",
    "\n",
    "# Categorize 'Predicted' and 'Original' columns and replace the values\n",
    "df6['Predicted'] = pd.cut(df6['Predicted'], bins=bins, labels=categories)\n",
    "df6['Original'] = pd.cut(df6['Original'], bins=bins, labels=categories)\n",
    "\n",
    "df6"
